						<div id="post-232" class="post-232 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog tag-book-cliffhanger-myths tag-book-sequels tag-book-series tag-contemporary-romance tag-fifteen-weekends-a-novel-by-christy-pastore tag-fifteen-weekends-is-a-fantastic-summer-read tag-is-fifteen-weekends-a-series tag-suspense">
	<h1 class="entry-title post-title">Is Fifteen Weekends A Series?</h1>
<div class="post-meta">
	<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author posted">Posted on </span><a href="http://christypastore-author.com/is-fifteen-weekends-a-series/" title="3:49 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="timestamp updated">June 19, 2014</span></a><span class="byline"> by </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://christypastore-author.com/author/christy-pastore/" title="View all posts by Christy Pastore">Christy Pastore</a></span>
			<span class="comments-link">
		<span class="mdash">&mdash;</span>
			<a href="http://christypastore-author.com/is-fifteen-weekends-a-series/#comments" title="Comment on Is Fifteen Weekends A Series?">2 Comments &darr;</a>		</span>
	</div><!-- end of .post-meta -->
				<div class="post-entry">
					<div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style addthis_32x32_style" addthis:url='http://christypastore-author.com/is-fifteen-weekends-a-series/' addthis:title='Is Fifteen Weekends A Series? ' ><a class="addthis_button_facebook"></a><a class="addthis_button_twitter"></a><a class="addthis_button_email"></a><a class="addthis_button_pinterest_share"></a><a class="addthis_button_compact"></a><a class="addthis_counter addthis_bubble_style"></a></div><p>The million dollar question: <strong>&#8220;Is Fifteen Weekends A Series?&#8221;</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://christypastore-author.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/well-this-sucks.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-237 aligncenter" alt="well this sucks" src="http://christypastore-author.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/well-this-sucks.jpg" width="394" height="243" /></a></p>
<p>Firstly, THANK YOU to everyone who has purchased and read Fifteen Weekends. It&#8217;s a total blast to be on this journey with all of you. I love receiving messages from readers, telling me how much they loved the book, and which story lines and characters are their favorites. Talking about Vince, Ethan and Liam brings a huge smile to my face. They are definitely a trifecta of some swoon worthy men.</p>
<p>The burning question at hand&#8211;<strong>will you be writing a follow up?</strong> Honestly, I would LOVE nothing more than to write a sequel to Fifteen Weekends!</p>
<p>But Christy, <strong>why didn&#8217;t you shop Fifteen Weekends as a series?</strong> Good question, and here is my long winded answer: I didn&#8217;t know that the book would be picked up so quickly! Imagine my surprise and shock when I got the call from Pen Name Publishing with that news?Â  I was all set to self-publish the book earlier this year. I guess you could say I got an offer I couldn&#8217;t refuse.</p>
<p><strong>How could I possibly not want to continue the story?</strong> I think Fifteen Weekends is a fantastic story, there is a notebook filled with developed plot lines, and I have already written a few pages! If you feel you need closure with the characters of course I want to give that to you!</p>
<p>If you loved the book tell your friends, write a review or better yet gift a book lover with Fifteen Weekends! Again, I cannot stress enough how much I appreciate and am overwhelmed by the tremendous support you have given to me and to this book that I so dearly love.</p>
<div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style " addthis:url='http://christypastore-author.com/is-fifteen-weekends-a-series/' addthis:title='Is Fifteen Weekends A Series? '  ><a class="addthis_button_facebook_like" fb:like:layout="button_count"></a><a class="addthis_button_tweet"></a><a class="addthis_button_pinterest_pinit"></a><a class="addthis_counter addthis_pill_style"></a></div>
